-- Moby Delays Italy Initial Share Offer, May Revive Sale When Markets Permit
-- Marco Bertacche
-- 2010-06-15T15:21:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/moby-delays-italy-initial-share-offer-may-revive-sale-when-markets-permit.html

          
          
             Moby SpA said it’s postponing an
initial public offering planned for coming weeks because of
current market conditions.  
 “The interest to revive the sale in the near future
remains alive,” Vincenzo Onorato, chairman of ferry operator
Moby, said in an e-mailed statement today.  
          
          


  


        